I"E<h1 id="spring-integration">Spring Integration</h1>

<p>Liquibase can be run in a <a href="http://www.springframework.org">Spring</a> environment by declaring a liquibase.spring.SpringLiquibase bean.</p>

<h2 id="example">Example</h2>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-xml" data-lang="xml"><span class="nt">&lt;bean</span> <span class="na">id=</span><span class="s">"liquibase"</span> <span class="na">class=</span><span class="s">"liquibase.integration.spring.SpringLiquibase"</span><span class="nt">&gt;</span>
      <span class="nt">&lt;property</span> <span class="na">name=</span><span class="s">"dataSource"</span> <span class="na">ref=</span><span class="s">"myDataSource"</span> <span class="nt">/&gt;</span>
      <span class="nt">&lt;property</span> <span class="na">name=</span><span class="s">"changeLog"</span> <span class="na">value=</span><span class="s">"classpath:db-changelog.xml"</span> <span class="nt">/&gt;</span>

      <span class="c">&lt;!--
      contexts specifies the runtime contexts to use.
      --&gt;</span>
      <span class="nt">&lt;property</span> <span class="na">name=</span><span class="s">"contexts"</span> <span class="na">value=</span><span class="s">"test, production"</span> <span class="nt">/&gt;</span>
 <span class="nt">&lt;/bean&gt;</span></code></pre></figure>

<h2 id="available-attributes">Available Attributes</h2>

<ul>
  <li>beanName</li>
  <li>changeLog</li>
  <li>contexts</li>
  <li>dataSource</li>
  <li>defaultSchema</li>
  <li>dropFirst <strong>since 2.0.2</strong></li>
  <li>parameters</li>
  <li>resourceLoader</li>
</ul>
